Recall you memory on past implementations made to project and give an status on last implementation.

Based on my memory, the last implementation focused on setting up the foundational CSS structure using SCSS. This involved:

1.  Creating `_variables.scss` to define the project's color palette.
2.  Creating SCSS partials: `_header.scss`, `_footer.scss`, and `_hero.scss`.
3.  Importing these partials into the main `main.scss` file to ensure they are compiled and applied to the site.

The basic structure for styling the header, footer, and hero sections is now in place.
Want to change the header_nav item 'Blog' to 'Notes', it links '/blog/' to '/notes/' and even the 'blog.md' to 'notes.md'

Okay, I will change 'Blog' to 'Notes', update the link from '/blog/' to '/notes/', and rename 'blog.md' to 'notes.md'.

Here is my plan:

1.  I'll read `src/_data/nav.json` to identify the navigation item to modify.
2.  I'll replace "Blog" with "Notes" and "/blog/" with "/notes/" in `src/_data/nav.json`.
3.  I'll rename `src/pages/blog.md` to `src/pages/notes.md`.
4.  I'll read the content of the newly renamed `src/pages/notes.md`.
5.  Finally, I'll update the content of `src/pages/notes.md` to reflect the change from "Blog" to "Notes".

I will now proceed with the first step.
